caption: Love this spot for sushi - convenient to my house and fairly priced. Never disappointed!

Very friendly owner and staff. I  am an ardent fan of their Mee Goreng, curry puff and Banana Leaves Rice (or we call it Nasi Lemak).  This is the place to go to for some comfort food.   I will take picture next round, we were too eager to dive into the food. :)  I ordered from Banana Leaves again. This time, I managed to take a picture; tough holding my troop back from Yummy-licous food! From left to right (clockwise): curry puff, mango sticky rice dessert, Kimchi bacon fried rice, mee goreng (shrimp) and drunken noodle (in the centre). The one at 6 o'clock is curry puff again, bought 2 servings of it!
Friendly and helpful on the phone.  Been going here for years.  Nice staff and good food.  Recommend...
I absolutely love this place. Great prices and delicious food! Try the steamed buns and the pad Thai.
Go to spot for Asian cuisine. Everything is delicious, however the specialty sushi rolls are my favorite. They are sublime and easily the best sushi I've had in DC.

Some of the most authentic tasting Asian food in the Baltimore/DC area. Must try the Thai coffee, laksa and japanese pizza! Will gladly drive down from Baltimore area again just for carryout again.  Super nice people too!
So good!! Don’t be deceived thinking since they have sushi and Chinese that it’s not good. Spicy curry shrimp isn’t spicy. It’s amazing. Full of flavor.  Laksa is incredible!
Foods are not specificly my taste but rest of my friends liked it. The ambiance is good and it's quite pricy
Staff are friendly and the food is yummy.
Great, fast service. Good food. Reasonable prices. Went there for lunch and had a good meal within the hour I had to be there.
Banana rum pineapple cocktail was great. Steamed buns, peanut sauce were excellent.

Located in the heart of Washington DC amazing Asian fusion restaurant. It is close to where a lot of the embassies are. Service is fast. Food is good. Sushi is well done. I would still recommend trying everything other than the sushi on the menu it is. Sushi is also great.  The restaurant is small and does get busy. A few minutes before lunch or a few minutes after will give you very good access.
We had the bento box dinner and left full and happy.
Great menu and food

This place is the best. It’s in my neighborhood (North DuPont) so convenient to walk to but parking on the surrounding side streets shouldn’t be too bad either. Great food. Great selection- Sushi, bento boxes, Thai, other entrees. Really good service. And bogo HH Mon-Fri, 5-7. It’s always low key when we go and we’re seated right away. This place is truly a gem. Inside seating only so no pets.
Banana Leaves is hands-down one of the friendliest, most accommodating, and tastiest Asian-fare restaurants in DC! The sushi is top notch, cocktails are delicious, and the staff is super nice.
So so
Various "look like" asian food

The wait staff is very friendly and courteous. However the food is just ok, nothing special. Spicy is barely spicy. The spring roll was very bland, along with the sweet and "spicy" sauce that came with it. I also had the vegetable hot pot which felt like it was a bit too heavy on miso as it was super super salty. My friend had the chicken pad kee maw which was a surprisingly small portion. There are much better, much more flavorful Asian restaurants right around the corner. I was kind of bummed that they didn't have any noodle dish vegetarian. And the vegetarian section was nothing to write home about.
One of my favorites. Great food, nice atmosphere!

This place never stops impressing me !! So far we have tried other place and were never as this satisfied and always come back here. Absolutely delicious,fast delivery and if the driver is ever running a bit late, will text to let us know. It happened once but he was still actually within the estimated delivery time they gave us. Thank you Banana Leaves for making our lazy cooking nights,amazing.
Cozy and romantic environment with good food, great cocktails and moderate prices.

Fresh, abundant, great value for a fantastic business lunch. All the right flavors from across Asia. I love the wait staff and the different options that offer a world of flavors that excite the sprit , satisfies the stomach , and pleases the eye.
Great food.
Best crab rangoons in DC!

The food and atmosphere is awesome. Waiter is polite and professional. Going out of his way to make your experience pleasant.  However the manager was a little on the rough side; (hurry up and order.  what do you need. rush! rush! I have better things to do.) "Ms. Tough Cookie" But I can see through the HARD crispy surface to the soft gooey heart.  Great place to eat.

Great little sushi and Thai restaurant that I have eaten at twice from out of town (San Diego). Great bento box selections and the Pad Thai was very tasty and a huge lunch portion. Great service, very friendly owner and staff.
Well prepared food

Amazing atmosphere, fresh food and very tasty in a very quaint locationin DC! Highly recommended. The Mango Sticky Rice was the best. We will return!
Food was spot on. Service great. If looking for a drink, the Woowoo is delicious
Very nice small restaurant with very good menu. Food was prepared quickly and was very tasty, not to oily and well cooked.
I got a bento box, it was pretty good. Quick service and friendly staff. I haven't had any entrees yet.
Fantastic Okonomiyaki. Great food at reasonable prices. Can't wait to return.
I've never been able to find Sate' without cooking it myself.  This place made me feel at home great food
I ordered the crab fried-rice and dumplings. The quality was excellent. Fresh ingredients, cooked on the spot and tasted great. The place is perfect for solo eating, small groups or take out.

I order banana leaves regularly for delivery and have eaten in the restaurant a couple of times.  The food is standard but just tastes clean.  The drunken noodles and Ka Prow are two of my favorites in the city. They don't way you down and do not taste slimy like you normally get with these dishes.  The sushi is good and they have a few unique rolls you should try.
The Pad Thai was to die for! The noodles were light and fresh. Sushi was extremely fresh and tasty and the Seasame Shrimp was so flavorful and tasty. Definitely would recommend.
Nice restaurant, really good dishes we got a good service... soda refills are not free so be careful on that, each soda is almost $6 wish they told us that since the beginning.
Great service, well prepared food, excellent flavors. Would highly recommend it and we will go back.
Great food. Friendly staff.
Better than average food and reasonable charges. Decent thai dishes and crispy malaysian roti pratha
Excellant Japanese box lunch with green  tea

Thank you to the entire Banana Leaves staff, especially Yen, for taking such good care of us last night. Our Michigan State University dinner was a success and we couldn't have done it without your wonderful team making sure that we were all well taken care of. The service was awesome, the food, always delicious, and your management's caring nature makes this one of my favorite spots in the city. I look forward to my next visit. See you in May!

I have to say I was very happy with my service when I came for dinner Saturday 1/26/19. I had General Tso's Chicken (average but good). It wasn't until 5AM the next day that I found out that everyone in my group who ate chicken (my meal, chicken fried rice, etc.) had gotten FOOD POISONING. I was terribly sick for over 24 hours and finally recovered today to write this. The manager said I could have 50% off my next meal because of this but I have to tell you I'm never coming back here.

The initial star was actually an accidental posting from a google phone, but I've corrected! I'm holding back on 5 stars because my friend and I were brought pork dumplings despite us requesting everything be vegetarian since I don't eat pork and my friend is practically vegan. The waitress was barely apologetic and didn't seem to understand why we didn't want the pork dumplings. Food was mostly decent, service was just okay.
Reasonable, clean, and modern. Good food too.
One of my favorite place for sushi and Thai food in the city! They have a lot of different types of Asian cuisines and everything is always really good. The tom kha and the crazy roll are so good!!!
Great food and service.

The meal was good. Quick service. Nice environment.
Good food. Service could be better.

Great service, really good sushi! The waitress was very friendly, polite, and attentive. Had a nice, quiet atmosphere that was perfect for having a decent conversation with a friend. Very relaxed, mellow vibe.  The sushi was excellent. If I had a complaint, it would be that the fresh salmon roll could have been a little more flavorful/fatty. Bit that's a minor quibble and I would definitely come here again.
Excellent!

Excellent. Best in a long time. Plenty of vegetarian options.
So good. I am looking forward to being a regular. The child that I had with me is very particular and the server was great with them. Our food was delicious. I can't wait to go back!
Best dumplings ever!

Ordered the curry special with chicken and was not even mildly impressed; very plain with little flavor, curry extremely watery, only redeeming trait was coconut rice was good. However, what really disappointed me was the "indian pancakes" I ordered were just regular storebought frozen pancakes they heated up (I know this because I literally have the exact same one in my freezer right now). Sad that they can get away with this lack of effort with their customers. Really one star, but giving two stars because delivery driver was nice

A great place to go get sushi you will love it
Great sushi 🍣 Good service!!!

Pan-Asian food served quickly from a large menu. The restaurant is located in a brownstone, with steep concrete steps. The sushi chef and his work area takes up about one-half of the first floor. The menu contains at least ten vegan entrees. It also includes many Pan-Asian items. I had Kung Pao Tofu. It was good. Prices are moderate. The second floor bathroom requires a steep walk-up. Not wheelchair accessible. Street parking.
Great place

I wish I came here more often.  A solid lunch spot, everything on the menu is very good. You simply cannot go wrong between the sushi, curry, noodles, or frankly anything else.  Many pan-Asian places do one type of food well and mail it in on the rest, but not Banana leaves (though if you want really authentic fare, do look elsewhere). For a sit-down place, the prices are pretty decent.
Ok

Located one block from the Washington Hilton Hotel and Connecticut Ave. Elegant upscale Asian atmosphere. First floor sushi dining area and bar with an upstairs main dining area. Menu options are from different asian regions.  Portions are small to average, tasty and a little pricy. Service is excellent with attention to details and customer service.
Only Asian restaurant in DC where you can get scallion pancakes!
Flavorful foods, very filling. Tasty curry and drunken noodles. Good Thai tea. Friendly service.

Everything was tasty and well done...from the old fashion to the fried rice.
My pineapple rice was pretty boring. The sushi looked good, drinks were good and came out quickly. They accommodated our birthday party and everyone sang, which was nice.
It was alright. The general Tso's chicken was very stringy, but had good flavor. Didn't eat their sushi, but a friend did, and it looked excellent.
Website said open all afternoon.  Walked here to find it closed until 5:00pm.

Good food but not exceptional
Food was delicious!

For a Saturday night it is quiet.  But that is okay with me.  I'm at the bar and another is here at the bar as well.  Tables are full but no wait.  People coming in to pick up take out seem like regulars which is a good sign.  No sushi chef hello!  I miss that.   Same as the Rikasa place I went to last night.   And where is the little cucumber salad chef treat?   Not here.  I miss that too.  The small things, right?  Sushi chefs are right at the door and should give a greeting.   Sushi restaurant 101.  Dirty menus but otherwise the place is clean. Could use a little more volume to the  background music but at least it is not too loud.  Lower is better than louder.  Service is prompt and courteous.  Food is FAST.  Miso soup is delish chauk full of tofu.  Could be a little warmer.  I like a very hot miso to sip.  Sushi arrived half way through Miso.  Too soon.  California Roll pieces are perfect size, but a little too big on nigiri sushi pieces.  California roll crabmeat is go my to be your basic - not freshly minced.  You know, you don't want too small but too big is difficult to eat in one bite.  These are only SLIGHTLY too big.    But excellent!  Fresh.  Great rice.   Your presentations is basic.  This is okay.  Nothing fancy here.  Ok.  This is a three in my opinion.   Very average.  Not bad.  I would definitely come back as a regular if I lived in the neighborhood.  It's a neighborhood hang out sushi pan Asian place.   Not a destination.
Very good flavours

Banana Leaves is a cute little restaurant with very yummy Asian food.  The dumplings taste so very good and the General Tso's chicken was so tasty. Did I mention the crab rangoon is also really tasty? Because it is! Mmmm mmm mmm.  Nom nom.
Great restaurant, been many times and it is (more often than not) delicious. I could eat 100 lbs of their naan
The service was fairly decent. The apps are delish, but my shrimp was served raw. Kind of turned my stomach. The server apologized
Fresh sushi
Tasty Asian food. Kind of a mix of  Thai, Japanese, and Malaysian on the menu but everything we had was good. Plus the service was better than the average.

This place gets the job done and the service is good. I usually get food that I end up not LOVING, but it's still good and tasty, and I eat it and enjoy it (and usually I blame my choices and not the food). I have yet to get the sushi here, but I have friends who love it. It's not super close to me, so it's not really worth a trek to go unless I'm meeting people.
Awesome place to get delivery in Dupont Circle. Try the Banana Leaves Rice dish which comes with baba curry and these delicious fried shrimp in a tangy orange sauce!

I went here for a business lunch and got the fried rice, my go-to whenever I hit up a Panasian restaurant. The food was good and our waitress was attentive, though the restaurant was a bit cramped feeling. The restaurant also offers a to-go and delivery, in case you don't want to dine in.
Absolutely delicious food with a lovely aestethic, flawless service, beautiful atmosphere, and reasonable prices. I can't wait to come back!
it was great. best won ton soup and  fried brown rice.
Lunch was great, the fried shitaki mushrooms were coated with an out of this world glaze. Thumbs up chef...
Your Avocado rolls make me feel like I am back home in California! Amazing! :)

Came here to start off our Saturday night in DC by grabbing a few sushi rolls to share and some unique cocktails (a little on the stronger side not that its a bad thing). The food itself was very good from the Tuna platter to the Uni everything was prepared very well and came out quickly to the table. The only issue I did have was after being seated it took 10+ minutes to get the servers attention so we could start ordering drinks and food. Besides this longer than usual wait to order everything was great and if you are in the area and looking for a decent priced sushi restaurant with good food then stop by. I recommend  the Spicy Tuna roll, or the yellowfin nigiri for the minimalist
Sushi is not good; tastes fishy and is stringy.  Satay is good though.
The Crab Ragoon Is always my favorite, though the rest of the menu is Fantastic! Hopefully they will expand there delivery area's in DC! Sometime's I would rather not drive to pick up my food!
Cozy atmosphere, excellent food, loved it!
Good curry laksa for lunch. Customer service efficient and discreet. Reasonable prices, good sake served hot. Definitely recommended.
Love the food and place. Most authentic Malaysian restaurant in DC.

Bearing in mind this was a Wednesday night, we had a very large party, which grew as the night went on. The service crew was able to accommodate.Our waiter (Herald or Henry..sorry) was excellent! He was very friendly and patient with our large group.  There is a small bar on the first floor which serves as a good meeting place while one awaits for people to arrive. The upstairs is tranquil and very good for conversation (not loud).  Food is a large variety of east Asian dishes from Malaysia to Korea. Everyone should be able to find something they like. I do recommend the hot pot but ask for it to be extra spicy, if you are a frequent hot pot consumer.

I used to order from here all the time. Loved the Spicy Crunchy Salmon Rolls and the Avocado Rolls. The last three time I ordered the Avocado was either hard and completely inedible or brown. Moving on the next sushi delivery spot...
